# Arc: Other | Scene: RazaphelQuestionsMage
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "No more games. I want to know what 'The Hollow World' is."
    new "No more games. I want to know what 'The Hollow World' is."

    old "The spirit moved through the air, silent for a while, as if considering its words."
    new "The spirit moved through the air, silent for a while, as if considering its words."

    old "When the old empire fell, the world collapsed into ruin behind it."
    new "When the old empire fell, the world collapsed into ruin behind it."

    old "Where its mighty roads once stretched to each corner of the world, uniting all the peoples under a single rule, it was now fragmented."
    new "Where its mighty roads once stretched to each corner of the world, uniting all the peoples under a single rule, it was now fragmented."

    old "Everywhere, small tyrants rose up, grasping at their chance to rule their corner of the world."
    new "Everywhere, small tyrants rose up, grasping at their chance to rule their corner of the world."

    old "None lasted long, for if there is one thing your world is not short on, it is men with avarice in their hearts."
    new "None lasted long, for if there is one thing your world is not short on, it is men with avarice in their hearts."

    old "The spirit drifted closer to her, its facemask focussing on her."
    new "The spirit drifted closer to her, its facemask focussing on her."

    old "The world became a cruel place for nearly a century. A world where only cruel men could thrive."
    new "The world became a cruel place for nearly a century. A world where only cruel men could thrive."

    old "And the institutions of old fell apart along with all the rest."
    new "And the institutions of old fell apart along with all the rest."

    old "Wise scholars. Great scientists. Brilliant legal minds. All were forced to work beneath the tyrant boot of Bandit Kings and robbers."
    new "Wise scholars. Great scientists. Brilliant legal minds. All were forced to work beneath the tyrant boot of Bandit Kings and robbers."

    old "And above all, even the great mage circles of old were not spared this debasement."
    new "And above all, even the great mage circles of old were not spared this debasement."

    old "Gone were their days of studies and scholastic pursuit. Instead, they were now simply weapons of war. Valuable ones at that."
    new "Gone were their days of studies and scholastic pursuit. Instead, they were now simply weapons of war. Valuable ones at that."

    old "And so the greatest of these Bandit Kings would eagerly recruit these mages for their power."
    new "And so the greatest of these Bandit Kings would eagerly recruit these mages for their power."

    old "And the mages, lacking any other option in this new and cruel world, traded power for easy living."
    new "And the mages, lacking any other option in this new and cruel world, traded power for easy living."

    old "Nearly a century, this debauched age carried on."
    new "Nearly a century, this debauched age carried on."

    old "The hearts of your race grew empty, for in a world of only survival, there is no place for ambition or dreams."
    new "The hearts of your race grew empty, for in a world of only survival, there is no place for ambition or dreams."

    old "Sarah saw the spirit rise up, closer to the ceiling of the cave."
    new "Sarah saw the spirit rise up, closer to the ceiling of the cave."

    old "This was the state of your world, nearly a century after the fall of the old empire."
    new "This was the state of your world, nearly a century after the fall of the old empire."

    old "And it was in this state that the eldest of their order drafted this book. 'The Hollow World'."
    new "And it was in this state that the eldest of their order drafted this book. 'The Hollow World'."

    old "Sarah remembered the thick tome. Its imposing presence."
    new "Sarah remembered the thick tome. Its imposing presence."

    old "He argued that the dissapearance of the Gods from your world was more than just a practical catastrophe."
    new "He argued that the dissapearance of the Gods from your world was more than just a practical catastrophe."

    old "The Gods, so he argued, did not only provide the foundation for the most elemental rules of your world, they also provided its moral foundation."
    new "The Gods, so he argued, did not only provide the foundation for the most elemental rules of your world, they also provided its moral foundation."

    old "The Gods judged each soul that passed through the world, condemning them to salvation or damnation, depending on their actions."
    new "The Gods judged each soul that passed through the world, condemning them to salvation or damnation, depending on their actions."

    old "Absent the Gods and their judgement, all souls now passed simply into nothingness."
    new "Absent the Gods and their judgement, all souls now passed simply into nothingness."

    old "A murderer and his victim, would equally go to the same place."
    new "A murderer and his victim, would equally go to the same place."

    old "In a world like that, empty of any final and objective moral foundation, there was only one natural conclusion. People lived for their own desires."
    new "In a world like that, empty of any final and objective moral foundation, there was only one natural conclusion. People lived for their own desires."

    old "So the Elder wrote that it was not an aberration that the world had collapsed into depravity."
    new "So the Elder wrote that it was not an aberration that the world had collapsed into depravity."

    old "Instead, he stated, in a world without Gods, it only made sense for the cruelest of men to inflict their brutalities on their victims."
    new "Instead, he stated, in a world without Gods, it only made sense for the cruelest of men to inflict their brutalities on their victims."

    old "To gather up as much fortune as they could. For what punishment awaited them in the next life? None at all."
    new "To gather up as much fortune as they could. For what punishment awaited them in the next life? None at all."

    old "Instead, there was only this life, and they lived it well while their victims writhed in agony."
    new "Instead, there was only this life, and they lived it well while their victims writhed in agony."

    old "And in the end, each went to the same nothingness."
    new "And in the end, each went to the same nothingness."

    old "Even hearing the description of this age made Sarah nervous."
    new "Even hearing the description of this age made Sarah nervous."

    old "With the absence of the Gods, the world had become 'Hollow', and it would not recover from this fatal fact."
    new "With the absence of the Gods, the world had become 'Hollow', and it would not recover from this fatal fact."

    old "Not unless they would one day return."
    new "Not unless they would one day return."

    old "The Gods, unbound by time and space, ushered back into this world could not only rebuild the foundation of the world."
    new "The Gods, unbound by time and space, ushered back into this world could not only rebuild the foundation of the world."

    old "They could reach back and resume all the injustices that had slipped by in their absence."
    new "They could reach back and resume all the injustices that had slipped by in their absence."

    old "To the Gods, returning all the dead souls from nothingness, and judging them, was no challenge at all."
    new "To the Gods, returning all the dead souls from nothingness, and judging them, was no challenge at all."

    old "Every unfortunate soul could be redeemed. Every wicked soul cast to the furnace."
    new "Every unfortunate soul could be redeemed. Every wicked soul cast to the furnace."

    old "All unpunished evils, made right."
    new "All unpunished evils, made right."

    old "To the Elder, the return of the Gods would mean not only the continuation of Justice for all future souls, but for all that ever existed."
    new "To the Elder, the return of the Gods would mean not only the continuation of Justice for all future souls, but for all that ever existed."

    old "When he had finished his book, he managed to deliver copies to nearly all the mages that still lived."
    new "When he had finished his book, he managed to deliver copies to nearly all the mages that still lived."

    old "The ideas spread among them like a disease."
    new "The ideas spread among them like a disease."

    old "And so, in the ruins of the capital of their old empire, the mages of the world gathered and renewed their Order."
    new "And so, in the ruins of the capital of their old empire, the mages of the world gathered and renewed their Order."

    old "Each vowed to forever forsake using their powers for cheap gain, to curse the Bandit Kings of the world, and to strive for one goal only..."
    new "Each vowed to forever forsake using their powers for cheap gain, to curse the Bandit Kings of the world, and to strive for one goal only..."

    old "Resumption. Emanation."
    new "Resumption. Emanation."

    old "The return of the Gods to your world and light anew the fires of divinity."
    new "The return of the Gods to your world and light anew the fires of divinity."

    old "Sarah remained quiet as she tried to take it all in."
    new "Sarah remained quiet as she tried to take it all in."

    old "Meanwhile, in my world, my Gods were equally blind as yours, and could not conceive of what was soon to happen."
    new "Meanwhile, in my world, my Gods were equally blind as yours, and could not conceive of what was soon to happen."

    old "So in turn, the Gods of your world blinded themselves even to their own nature."
    new "So in turn, the Gods of your world blinded themselves even to their own nature."

    old "Yes. Full of fire, your soul so bright it poured out of you like light from the stars, your hair blazing flame."
    new "Yes. Full of fire, your soul so bright it poured out of you like light from the stars, your hair blazing flame."

    old "When the barrier between the world was put up and my race was thrown underneath, I managed to escape."
    new "When the barrier between the world was put up and my race was thrown underneath, I managed to escape."

    old "Invisible to them, you can move against their designs."
    new "Invisible to them, you can move against their designs."

    old "But who was this spirit, truly? She sensed there was a truth in his words, but truth did not mean that he could not deceive."
    new "But who was this spirit, truly? She sensed there was a truth in his words, but truth did not mean that he could not deceive."

    old "The surface of it felt smooth. It was cold in a subtle, persistent way, reaching through even her gloves."
    new "The surface of it felt smooth. It was cold in a subtle, persistent way, reaching through even her gloves."

    old "The spark grew and grew, driving out and forcing away the cold."
    new "The spark grew and grew, driving out and forcing away the cold."

    old "Sarah willed the spirit to fade, and an in instant, the spirit was gone."
    new "Sarah willed the spirit to fade, and an in instant, the spirit was gone."

    old "Dear Sarah, old friend, I have never hated you. Even in the dreams where you held the power that condemned us."
    new "Dear Sarah, old friend, I have never hated you. Even in the dreams where you held the power that condemned us."

    old "She saw the frightened faces of scholars surrounding her."
    new "She saw the frightened faces of scholars surrounding her."

    old "Did the scaffolding break? What happened?"
    new "Did the scaffolding break? What happened?"

    old "Sarah waved her hand and pushed them away from herself."
    new "Sarah waved her hand and pushed them away from herself."

    old "She coughed up more of the sand."
    new "She coughed up more of the sand."

    old "Slowly, she managed to recover herself."
    new "Slowly, she managed to recover herself."

    old "I'm fine, I'm fine! Please, give me some space."
    new "I'm fine, I'm fine! Please, give me some space."

    old "She saw the scholars slowly back away from her."
    new "She saw the scholars slowly back away from her."

    old "Confusion in their faces. They were trying to figure out who she was. What she was doing here."
    new "Confusion in their faces. They were trying to figure out who she was. What she was doing here."

    old "Sarah had no good answers for them."
    new "Sarah had no good answers for them."

    old "Recovered enough, Sarah leapt up to her feet."
    new "Recovered enough, Sarah leapt up to her feet."

    old "She pushed her way passed the still startled scholars."
    new "She pushed her way passed the still startled scholars."

    old "Before they could say much more, she began to run."
    new "Before they could say much more, she began to run."

    old "Behind her, she could hear their voices. First calm, then swiftly rising."
    new "Behind her, she could hear their voices. First calm, then swiftly rising."

    old "Stop her!"
    new "Stop her!"

    old "Sarah was already halfway up the scaffolding, her feet racing."
    new "Sarah was already halfway up the scaffolding, her feet racing."

    old "She could feel the pain in her limbs; injuries from the fall. Considering the height, they felt trivial."
    new "She could feel the pain in her limbs; injuries from the fall. Considering the height, they felt trivial."

    old "She planted her feet, one after the other, swiftly, racing up the wooden construction."
    new "She planted her feet, one after the other, swiftly, racing up the wooden construction."

    old "More sounds of people calling out after her. Asking for someone to stop her. Nobody did."
    new "More sounds of people calling out after her. Asking for someone to stop her. Nobody did."

    old "Coming up over the edge of the pit, Sarah ran out across the road."
    new "Coming up over the edge of the pit, Sarah ran out across the road."

    old "The city spun around her, the ruins disorienting. Where. Where had she come from."
    new "The city spun around her, the ruins disorienting. Where. Where had she come from."

    old "Sarah closed her eyes and focussed."
    new "Sarah closed her eyes and focussed."

    old "She forced her mind to be calm. In the darkness of her mind, she reached out and felt the latent magical energy."
    new "She forced her mind to be calm. In the darkness of her mind, she reached out and felt the latent magical energy."

    old "The energy she'd left behind to guide her way back to the door through which she had come."
    new "The energy she'd left behind to guide her way back to the door through which she had come."

    old "Then she felt it."
    new "Then she felt it."

    old "Sarah opened her eyes, oriented herself towards the energy, and continued to run."
    new "Sarah opened her eyes, oriented herself towards the energy, and continued to run."

    old "By now, the shouts were growing louder and louder."
    new "By now, the shouts were growing louder and louder."

    old "She heard the rough and hard voices of soldiers. The clattering of boots against stone."
    new "She heard the rough and hard voices of soldiers. The clattering of boots against stone."

    old "Sarah made her way further down the road."
    new "Sarah made her way further down the road."

    old "She had a distance on them, she could make it before they would catch up to her. She just needed to keep running."
    new "She had a distance on them, she could make it before they would catch up to her. She just needed to keep running."

    old "Her feet raced under her, each step following the next."
    new "Her feet raced under her, each step following the next."

    old "Her lungs were burning, half from the exhaustion, half from the sand that was still in her lungs."
    new "Her lungs were burning, half from the exhaustion, half from the sand that was still in her lungs."

    old "Coughing, she continued to force herself to run."
    new "Coughing, she continued to force herself to run."

    old "Behind her, she could hear the sounds of soldiers coming closer."
    new "Behind her, she could hear the sounds of soldiers coming closer."

    old "She turned her hear around and saw the light of torches. Search parties."
    new "She turned her hear around and saw the light of torches. Search parties."

    old "Run. Run. Run."
    new "Run. Run. Run."

    old "Sarah repeated the words in her head like a mantra."
    new "Sarah repeated the words in her head like a mantra."

    old "Turning back to face in front of her, she suddenly felt her heart stop."
    new "Turning back to face in front of her, she suddenly felt her heart stop."

    old "A group of soldiers blocked the road up ahead of her."
    new "A group of soldiers blocked the road up ahead of her."

    old "Sarah stopped."
    new "Sarah stopped."

    old "For a brief moment, she expected them to call out to her, but judging by their body language, she could see they were still searching."
    new "For a brief moment, she expected them to call out to her, but judging by their body language, she could see they were still searching."

    old "They had their torches, but she was standing in the darkness. They missed her."
    new "They had their torches, but she was standing in the darkness. They missed her."

    old "Sarah quickly ran to the side of the road, jumping into one of the ruined homes that littered the city."
    new "Sarah quickly ran to the side of the road, jumping into one of the ruined homes that littered the city."

    old "She lowered her head and looked out over the edge of the broken wall that had one been a proper one."
    new "She lowered her head and looked out over the edge of the broken wall that had one been a proper one."

    old "The group of soldiers were discussing among themselves."
    new "The group of soldiers were discussing among themselves."

    old "More joined, the ones that been close behind her."
    new "More joined, the ones that been close behind her."

    old "Talking. Shouting."
    new "Talking. Shouting."

    old "She could hardly make it out, but they appeared animated."
    new "She could hardly make it out, but they appeared animated."

    old "A few wobbled about, clearly drunk."
    new "A few wobbled about, clearly drunk."

    old "They had not been expecting to have to do any real work tonight, that much was clear to her."
    new "They had not been expecting to have to do any real work tonight, that much was clear to her."

    old "Looking at the soldiers, Sarah estimated there were about twenty of them, give or take."
    new "Looking at the soldiers, Sarah estimated there were about twenty of them, give or take."

    old "The truth was, she didn't really fear them."
    new "The truth was, she didn't really fear them."

    old "She wasn't afraid of what would happen to her if they caught her."
    new "She wasn't afraid of what would happen to her if they caught her."

    old "She was afraid of what she would have to do to them."
    new "She was afraid of what she would have to do to them."

    old "Fight your way out"
    new "Fight your way out"

    old "Sarah saw the soldiers. Their search had only just begun."
    new "Sarah saw the soldiers. Their search had only just begun."

    old "She didn't have the time to wait here."
    new "She didn't have the time to wait here."

    old "Who knew, perhaps the longer she'd wait, the more soldiers would show up. Twenty she could handle, but more..."
    new "Who knew, perhaps the longer she'd wait, the more soldiers would show up. Twenty she could handle, but more..."

    old "Sarah took a deep breath and stilled her nerves."
    new "Sarah took a deep breath and stilled her nerves."

    old "Think of what they'd do to you, if they had the chance, Sarah thought."
    new "Think of what they'd do to you, if they had the chance, Sarah thought."

    old "What little mercy she had for them, vanished."
    new "What little mercy she had for them, vanished."

    old "Sarah leapt out from the ruins onto the road."
    new "Sarah leapt out from the ruins onto the road."

    old "She drew out the magical energies from within."
    new "She drew out the magical energies from within."

    old "By now, controlling them felt so easy, she wondered how she had even struggled with it at all."
    new "By now, controlling them felt so easy, she wondered how she had even struggled with it at all."

    old "Tendrils of raw magical energy came into focus, wrapping around her body and lifting her up into the air."
    new "Tendrils of raw magical energy came into focus, wrapping around her body and lifting her up into the air."

    old "Floating a small distance above the ground, she drew in a deep breath."
    new "Floating a small distance above the ground, she drew in a deep breath."

    old "Then she breathed out fire."
    new "Then she breathed out fire."

    old "The pale blue flame rushed out from her throat and poured down onto the first group of soldiers like lava."
    new "The pale blue flame rushed out from her throat and poured down onto the first group of soldiers like lava."

    old "Sarah could hear their screams, drowned out only by the intense heat."
    new "Sarah could hear their screams, drowned out only by the intense heat."

    old "The other soldiers reacted with horror."
    new "The other soldiers reacted with horror."

    old "They had been searching for an odd, defenseless girl. None of them had signed up to fight a mage."
    new "They had been searching for an odd, defenseless girl. None of them had signed up to fight a mage."

    old "Sarah twisted her hand. The blue flame twisted to her every command, rushing out from the first victims and leaping onto the next."
    new "Sarah twisted her hand. The blue flame twisted to her every command, rushing out from the first victims and leaping onto the next."

    old "More victims. More screams. More melting flesh."
    new "More victims. More screams. More melting flesh."

    old "Sarah looked down from above as five of the soldiers laid dead, their corpses burning."
    new "Sarah looked down from above as five of the soldiers laid dead, their corpses burning."

    old "A haunting blue light had drowned out all other light."
    new "A haunting blue light had drowned out all other light."

    old "The magical light painted their horrified faces in silver."
    new "The magical light painted their horrified faces in silver."

    old "Then they ran."
    new "Then they ran."

    old "Sarah closed her eyes and was happy. Happy that they wouldn't force her to do more."
    new "Sarah closed her eyes and was happy. Happy that they wouldn't force her to do more."

    old "Their screams rang out, but they ran so fast that before long, she couldn't hear them anymore."
    new "Their screams rang out, but they ran so fast that before long, she couldn't hear them anymore."

    old "Sarah severed the tendrils that kept her lifted above the ground."
    new "Sarah severed the tendrils that kept her lifted above the ground."

    old "Falling back down, she gracefully landed, her knees bending to soften her fall."
    new "Falling back down, she gracefully landed, her knees bending to soften her fall."

    old "Around her, the smell of her carnage."
    new "Around her, the smell of her carnage."

    old "What of it, she thought. They'd have done worse to her if they could. She knew that to be true."
    new "What of it, she thought. They'd have done worse to her if they could. She knew that to be true."

    old "Sarah began to ran."
    new "Sarah began to ran."

    old "She had caused too much commotion and before long, more soldiers would come. Fools who might hope to kill a mage."
    new "She had caused too much commotion and before long, more soldiers would come. Fools who might hope to kill a mage."

    old "Sarah wanted to be gone before they came, lest she'd have to kill more."
    new "Sarah wanted to be gone before they came, lest she'd have to kill more."

    old "She ran through the streets and following the traces of energy she'd left behind, she came upon the house where she had first entered."
    new "She ran through the streets and following the traces of energy she'd left behind, she came upon the house where she had first entered."

    old "The ruined house was undisturbed."
    new "The ruined house was undisturbed."

    old "Sarah quickly oriented herself. Outside she began to hear voices again. More fools."
    new "Sarah quickly oriented herself. Outside she began to hear voices again. More fools."

    old "She placed her hand against the broken wall and began to feel."
    new "She placed her hand against the broken wall and began to feel."

    old "For a moment, her fingers gripped only stone and air."
    new "For a moment, her fingers gripped only stone and air."

    old "A moment longer, and her heart began to race."
    new "A moment longer, and her heart began to race."

    old "Was it gone? Could it be?"
    new "Was it gone? Could it be?"

    old "Then, her hand wrapped around something she could not see, but only feel."
    new "Then, her hand wrapped around something she could not see, but only feel."

    old "She pulled."
    new "She pulled."

    old "Appearing from nothingness, a door swung open."
    new "Appearing from nothingness, a door swung open."

    old "Inside...home."
    new "Inside...home."

    old "Sarah jumped through and slammed the door behind her."
    new "Sarah jumped through and slammed the door behind her."

    old "Stay hidden"
    new "Stay hidden"

    old "It wasn't worth it to try and run."
    new "It wasn't worth it to try and run."

    old "If they caught her, she'd have no choice but to fight them. If she waited, she was sure they'd move on."
    new "If they caught her, she'd have no choice but to fight them. If she waited, she was sure they'd move on."

    old "For a while longer, Sarah sat and watched."
    new "For a while longer, Sarah sat and watched."

    old "One by one, the group of soldiers broke down into smaller groups, heading into different directions."
    new "One by one, the group of soldiers broke down into smaller groups, heading into different directions."

    old "Then, when the last group moved out, she saw the perfect opportunity."
    new "Then, when the last group moved out, she saw the perfect opportunity."

    old "If she ran now, she could make it."
    new "If she ran now, she could make it."

    old "Before long, more soldiers would come. Fools who might hope to kill a mage."
    new "Before long, more soldiers would come. Fools who might hope to kill a mage."

    old "Sarah wanted to be gone before they tried."
    new "Sarah wanted to be gone before they tried."

    old "Wait longer"
    new "Wait longer"

    old "Sitting in the dark, Sarah continued to watch the road up ahead."
    new "Sitting in the dark, Sarah continued to watch the road up ahead."

    old "The house she was looking for was somewhere in that direction."
    new "The house she was looking for was somewhere in that direction."

    old "The road seemed clear enough by now."
    new "The road seemed clear enough by now."

    old "Sarah began to move, but only one step outside of her hiding place, and a voice rang out."
    new "Sarah began to move, but only one step outside of her hiding place, and a voice rang out."

    old "Sarah turned towards the voice."
    new "Sarah turned towards the voice."

    old "Two soldiers came walking up towards her."
    new "Two soldiers came walking up towards her."

    old "Sarah back away from them, back into the ruined house, but before she knew it, they followed her inside."
    new "Sarah back away from them, back into the ruined house, but before she knew it, they followed her inside."

    old "One walked inside, while the other blocked the door."
    new "One walked inside, while the other blocked the door."

    old "Sarah cursed herself for having waited too long."
    new "Sarah cursed herself for having waited too long."

    old "You know, we were havin a pretty good night before they pulled us out from the party and told us to go on patrol duty."
    new "You know, we were havin a pretty good night before they pulled us out from the party and told us to go on patrol duty."

    old "And they say go look for some blonde girl causin trouble down at the digsite."
    new "And they say go look for some blonde girl causin trouble down at the digsite."

    old "He eyed her up and down."
    new "He eyed her up and down."

    old "You don't seem like the type that can cause much trouble."
    new "You don't seem like the type that can cause much trouble."

    old "Sarah's eyes drifted from one soldier to the other."
    new "Sarah's eyes drifted from one soldier to the other."

    old "Just two. She could handle them."
    new "Just two. She could handle them."

    old "But it wasn't just a question of handling them."
    new "But it wasn't just a question of handling them."

    old "Her magic was powerful, but it was far from subtle. If she burned her way through these two, how many others would rush towards her?"
    new "Her magic was powerful, but it was far from subtle. If she burned her way through these two, how many others would rush towards her?"

    old "How many more would she have to kill on her way out?"
    new "How many more would she have to kill on her way out?"

    old "Now, my buddy and I here caught you, so I guess we'll be doin the interrogation. Sounds fair?"
    new "Now, my buddy and I here caught you, so I guess we'll be doin the interrogation. Sounds fair?"

    old "Kill the soldiers"
    new "Kill the soldiers"

    old "Sarah only shook her head."
    new "Sarah only shook her head."

    old "Let me go and we won't have any trouble."
    new "Let me go and we won't have any trouble."

    old "Try to stop me, and you'll regret it. Sounds fair?"
    new "Try to stop me, and you'll regret it. Sounds fair?"

    old "Had she been any ordinary girl, a threat like hers would have meant nothing to him."
    new "Had she been any ordinary girl, a threat like hers would have meant nothing to him."

    old "Sarah took two steps forward when the soldier suddenly reached out and grabbed her arm."
    new "Sarah took two steps forward when the soldier suddenly reached out and grabbed her arm."

    old "She snapped her fingers and the blue fire rushed up his arm, crawling into the crevices in his armor."
    new "She snapped her fingers and the blue fire rushed up his arm, crawling into the crevices in his armor."

    old "He collapsed to the ground, screaming as the fire rushed over him."
    new "He collapsed to the ground, screaming as the fire rushed over him."

    old "Sarah looked towards the other soldier."
    new "Sarah looked towards the other soldier."

    old "She held up the magical flame in her hand."
    new "She held up the magical flame in her hand."

    old "The light danced on his face for a moment, showing his horror."
    new "The light danced on his face for a moment, showing his horror."

    old "He dropped his weapons and began to ran."
    new "He dropped his weapons and began to ran."

    old "Sarah was relieved she'd only have to kill the arrogant one."
